                            <comment id="12845418" author="daijy" created="Mon, 15 Mar 2010 17:30:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In SkewedPartitioner.java, we have:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;return (Math.abs(keyTuple.hashCode()) % totalReducers);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In javadoc, we have the note:&lt;br/&gt;
Math.abs(int): if the argument is equal to the value of Integer.MIN_VALUE, the most negative representable int value, the result is that same value, which is negative.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We hit exactly the same situation in this case.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
